dataRoles.description: Enter the column that holds your your point data name or territory (markup) name. Required for mapping data.
dataRoles.name: eztTerritoryData

dataRoles.description: Enter the column that contains the numeric values or text values that you would like to classify on.
dataRoles.name: eztAggregatedData

dataRoles.description: Enter the column that holds your territory (markup) Primary Key.
dataRoles.name: eztPrimaryKey

dataRoles.description: Enter additional data that will be included in the tool tip.
dataRoles.name: Tooltips

dataRoles.description: Enter the columns that you would like to add as hyperlinks in the point layer callout.
dataRoles.name: hyperlinks

dataRoles.description: Required for mapping point data. If you have duplicate records (based on the column you entered in the 'Name column') in your data set, you need to change the aggregate type to 'average'. Not required for territory data (polygons).
dataRoles.name: pointLat

dataRoles.description: Required for mapping point data. If you have duplicate records (based on the column you entered in the 'Name column') in your data set, you need to change the aggregate type to 'average'. Not required for territory data (polygons).
dataRoles.name: pointLon

dataRoles.description: Sets the size of the point radius
dataRoles.name: eztPointSize

dataRoles.description: Set this if you have multiple projects in your EZT Hierarchy table and want to view territories from multiple projects in visual.
dataRoles.name: projectIds

displayLegend.description: Makes the legend expanded (visible) on report load.

maxSelection.description: Max selection count on drawing tool or travel ring.

territoryColors.description: Optionally turn 'On' to synchronize data point colors between this visual and other visuals in your report. You must also have the same field in 'Aggregated Field Column' in this visual as the 'Values' fields column in out-of-the-box Power BI Visuals.

territoryOpacity.description: Define a number between 0 and 1 to set the territory opacity.

territoryBorderWidth.description: Define a number between 0 and 4 to set the size of the territory border.

territoryBorderColor.description: Define a number between 0 and 4 to set the size of the territory border.

territoryLabels.description: Select from the dropdown whether you would like dynamic or fixed labels on top of your territories. Dynamic labels change position based on zoom level. Fixed labels are static and are positioned based on label positions from your EasyTerritory project. For fixed labels you must have visible labels enabled, saved (with plugin executed) in your EasyTerritory project.

size.description: Define a number between 0 and 50 to set the size of the territory labels

maxZoom.description: Define a number between 0 and 24 to set the maximum zoom level the labels will be visible

minZoom.description: Define a number between 0 and 24 to set the minimum zoom level the labels will be visible

pointSymbolType.description: Define the type of point symbol you would like to be display on map.

fill.description: Define the color you would like to be set for the circle symbol on the point layer.

pointOpacity.description: Define a number between 0 and 1 to set the point opacity

size.description: Define a number between 1 and 50 to be set point radius.

pointBorderColor.description: Define the color you would like to be set for the point border.

pointBorderSize.description: Define the size you would like to be set for the point border.

sizeClassify.description: Define a number between 10 and 50 to be set largest point radius.

clusterPoints.description: Cluster points when map is zoomed out to improve readability when large data points are loaded to map.

clusterRadius.description: Enter a number that will set the radius, in pixels, that nearby points will be grouped into a cluster.

clusterMaxZoom.description: Enter a number that will set maximum zoom level in which clustering occurs.

clusterPieChart.description: Cluster points as a pie chart.

eztClassifyOn.description: Turn 'On' to do a classification based on the values from the 'Classification Column' in this visual.

eztClassifyBreakType.description: Set to 'equal-interval' for value ranges in each classification to be equal in size. Set to 'quantile' for equal number of points or territoires in each classification.

eztClassifyType.description: Set to 'static' for classification classes to persist regardless of filters or slicers on report. Set to 'dynamic' to modify the classification classes based on the filtering or slicing the source data.

eztClassify.description: Select how many number of classes or groups you would like to divide the 'Aggregated Field Column' values into. Cannot exceed the number of class breaks available in your data

eztColorGrad.description: Select what color you would like the color gradient to be.

eztColorGradExact.description: Select what color you would like the color gradient to be.

groupLevel6.description: Copy your group level 6 column name in your hierachy and paste it here.

groupLevel1.description: Copy your group level 1 column name in your hierachy and paste it here.

groupLevel.description: Copy your group level column name in your hierachy and paste it here.

territoryLevel.description: Copy your territory level column name in your hierachy and paste it here.

partLevel.description: Copy your part level column name in your hierachy and paste it here.

opacity.description: Specify a number between 1 and 10 to set the opacity of the weather tile layers
